# Force LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# ConfigBroker ships committed sample artefacts (out/resolved.env,
# out/audit.log, and the sbom/ family). The compiler emits the SBOMs with
# LF on every OS, and the WASI backend writes the resolved config and the
# audit log with LF too, so the only way a regenerated tree could differ
# from what ships here is a checkout that rewrote committed LF to CRLF
# (core.autocrlf). Every tracked file is text (.capa, .json, .env, .log,
# .asc, .tsv, .md, .toml, .sh, LICENSE, SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH); a blanket
# eol=lf is safe and keeps the reproducibility diff empty.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Reproducibility inputs, pinned LF for defence in depth.
sbom/SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH text eol=lf
generate.sh            text eol=lf
